#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""generate-quality-dashboard — Quality dashboard for the 25-niche pipeline.

Reads QUALITY_METRICS.yaml, FRESHNESS_VIOLATION_LOG.yaml, TOOL_ERROR_LOG.yaml,
and SLI_DEFINITIONS.yaml. Produces a summary report with:
  - SLI compliance (6 SLIs against their targets)
  - Staleness hotspots (per-data-type staleness rates + trend)
  - Error-prone tools (per-tool error counts and top error types)
  - Evidence quality trend (per-niche sequence + linear trend)
  - Wall-clock drift (actual vs. estimated per niche)
  - Alert status (warning/critical threshold checks)
  - Auto-generated recommendations (heuristic rules)

Run after every 5th niche, or on demand with --since NICHE_ID
for incremental dashboards.

Usage:
    ./generate-quality-dashboard [--output FILE] [--format yaml|json|text] [--since NICHE_ID] [--dry-run]

Exit codes:
    0   SUCCESS           All checks pass, no critical alerts
    1   BLOCKED        (CRITICAL_ALERTS — one or more alerts firing above critical thresholds)
    2   WARNING           Degraded data sources (missing/corrupted YAML files)
    3   INTERNAL_ERROR    Script bug or missing dependency
    4   INVALID_INPUT     Invalid arguments
"""

